<br>
Hard drive based portable MP3 Players<br>
I-Pod (coolest) 5gig's presently with 10gig on the way. You CAN use it with Windows (there's a workaround). Do a Yahoo search for windows + i-Pod and you'll find the company that makes the software (apparently it works, but not flawlessly).<br>
<br>
d-link roq-it 10gig:<br>
New player. It is cheapest / largest capacity of the hard drive players. I read some of the early reviews and they were not entirely favorable.<br>
<br>
Creative Labs: Nomad<br>
Comes in several diff types 6gig, 20gig. Price is moderate (200 for 6gig up to 400 for 20gig). They're larger than some of the others, but fairly reliable, and has search function built in. I have a friend who works as a DJ and he uses 2 of these things linked through a mixing board. Nifty!<br>
<br>
Archos: Smaller than the nomad. Reviews have been fair.<br>
Price is similar to Nomad (slightly cheaper).<br>
<br>
All of these can be used to store mp3's AND files from your computer (including i-Pod) as if they were an external/portable hard drive (which, in fact, they are).<br>
<br>
I still haven't bought one...kind of waiting to see what new ones crop up. I may still buy a refurbished Nomad...<br>
<br>
